  <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:7pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;">Portrait One-Pager (8.5 × 11in)</p>
  <div class="layout-diagram">
    <div class="ld-header"><span class="ld-header-txt">Header — #08152A navy full-width · 4pt #185FA5 left border rule · POC panel right (#1E2D42)</span></div>
    <div class="ld-body">
      <div class="ld-left"><div class="ld-label">Left Col<br>2.05in<br>Mission Need<br>Workflow<br>Impact</div></div>
      <div class="ld-center"><div class="ld-label">Centre Col<br>flexible<br>Schematic / Diagram<br>Key Standards</div></div>
      <div class="ld-right"><div class="ld-label">Right Col<br>1.9in<br>Capabilities<br>Approach</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="ld-footer"><span class="ld-footer-txt">Footer — #F4F6F9 surface · brand left · ∃X.P(X) center watermark · stamp right</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-box warn" style="margin-bottom:12px;">
    <div class="rule-lbl">PDF Print Rule — CSS Grid Not Supported</div>
    <div class="rule-text">wkhtmltopdf uses an older WebKit engine. CSS Grid layouts collapse to single column in print mode. Use <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> with explicit column widths for all print/PDF deliverables. CSS Grid works correctly in modern browsers (Chrome print-to-PDF).</div>
  </div>

  <table class="tbl">
    <thead><tr><th>Document Type</th><th>Dimensions</th><th>Key Layout Rule</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Portrait one-pager</td><td>8.5 × 11in</td><td>3-column table. Approach section stacked vertically in right column.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Landscape one-pager</td><td>11 × 8.5in</td><td>3-column table. Approach becomes full-width horizontal timeline at page bottom.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Presentation (dark slide)</td><td>1280×720px (16:9)</td><td>Navy background only. For: Title, Transition, Close slides.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Presentation (light slide)</td><td>1280×720px (16:9)</td><td>White background. 3px blue left rule. Navy header bar.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>White paper</td><td>Letter, 1in margins</td><td>4.5in body / 1.75in sidebar / 0.25in gutter. Times New Roman body.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="rule-box">
    <div class="rule-lbl">Slide Hierarchy — Non-Negotiable</div>
    <div class="rule-text">Every presentation: Opens dark → transitions dark → closes dark. Body slides are light. Never open or close on a light slide. The structural rhythm — dark/light/dark — is intentional and brand-defining.</div>
  </div>
</div>

