      <div class="framing-item">
        "parent company"<br>
        "sister company"<br>
        "spun off from Galois" (implies separation)<br>
        "Galois vendor"<br>
        "we are Galois"
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:7pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;">Tagline Usage — Context-Specific</p>
  <div class="tagline-row">
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Tagline</div><div class="tagline-mark">"Never start at zero."</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Use for</div><div class="tagline-use">First contact. External audiences. Cold outreach. Capability briefs. Marketing materials.</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Never for</div><div class="tagline-never">Internal planning. After the relationship is established (sounds hollow).</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="tagline-row">
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Tagline</div><div class="tagline-mark">"The solution exists."</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Use for</div><div class="tagline-use">Narrative contexts. About page. Pitch decks after the problem is established.</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Never for</div><div class="tagline-never">Headlines. Opening statements. Cold email subject lines.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="tagline-row">
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Mark</div><div class="tagline-mark">∃X.P(X)</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Use for</div><div class="tagline-use">Visual watermark only. IBM Plex Mono, 4–6% opacity on dark surfaces. Mathematical confirmation.</div></div>
    <div><div class="tagline-lbl">Never for</div><div class="tagline-never">First impression. Cold outreach. Oral delivery. Full-opacity display. Explanation of itself.</div></div>
  </div>

  <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:7pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;margin-top:20px;">Anti-Persona — What ExistX Refuses to Be</p>
  <div class="anti-grid">
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">"Technology transition firm"</div><div class="anti-reason">Jargon. Undifferentiated. Every GovCon shop says this. Describes process, not mission.</div></div>
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">"GovCon software developer"</div><div class="anti-reason">Commodity framing. Implies staff augmentation. Undersells the research depth.</div></div>
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">"Startup"</div><div class="anti-reason">Signals instability. Use "defense-tech firm" or "mission-focused company."</div></div>
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">"Advise and leave"</div><div class="anti-reason">The core anti-pattern. ExistX deploys and sustains. Never implies consulting posture.</div></div>
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">Consumer tech aesthetic</div><div class="anti-reason">Rounded corners, pastel colors, emoji, illustration-heavy layouts. Incompatible with the brand.</div></div>
    <div class="anti-item"><div class="anti-label">Overpromise</div><div class="anti-reason">Never claim customer-validated outcomes not yet confirmed. Distinguish: demonstrated vs. deployed vs. planned.</div></div>
  </div>
</div>

