  <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:7pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;margin-top:20px;">Vocabulary — Avoid / Replace</p>
  <div style="background:#fff;border:0.5px solid var(--border);border-radius:4px;overflow:hidden;padding:0 14px;margin-bottom:16px;">
    <div style="display:flex;gap:0;padding:7px 0;border-bottom:0.5px solid var(--border);">
      <div style="width:200px;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:6.5pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);flex-shrink:0;">Avoid</div>
      <div style="width:200px;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:6.5pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);flex-shrink:0;padding-left:16px;">Replace with</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:6.5pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);">Reason</div>
    </div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"leverage"</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">"use" / be specific</div><div class="vocab-reason">Meaningless filler in professional contexts</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"innovative / cutting-edge"</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">Name the specific advance</div><div class="vocab-reason">Unproven claim. Name what is new and why.</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"solution" (as generic noun)</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">Name the capability</div><div class="vocab-reason">Every competitor says this. Be specific.</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"help" (as ExistX's role)</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">"operationalize" / "deploy"</div><div class="vocab-reason">Too soft. ExistX doesn't help — it executes.</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"best-in-class"</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">Prove it or omit</div><div class="vocab-reason">Unverifiable superlative. Credibility cost.</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"synergy / ecosystem"</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">Never</div><div class="vocab-reason">Corporate filler. Signals weak thinking.</div></div>
    <div class="vocab-row"><div class="vocab-avoid">"consult" (describing ExistX)</div><div class="vocab-use" style="padding-left:16px;">integrate / deploy / sustain</div><div class="vocab-reason">Core anti-pattern. ExistX is not a consultancy.</div></div>
  </div>

  <p style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:7pt;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px;">Epistemic Precision — Status Language</p>
  <table class="tbl">
    <thead><tr><th>Status</th><th>Approved Language</th><th>Never Say</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Confirmed, in production</td><td>"deployed," "operational," "in production"</td><td>"We've deployed..." without specifics</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Demonstrated on hardware</td><td>"demonstrated on physical PSIL hardware"</td><td>"proven" (implies broader validation)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Active development</td><td>"in active development," "Phase 1 target"</td><td>"coming soon," "launching soon"</td></tr>
      <tr><td>High-probability pending</td><td>"high-probability pending award," "imminent"</td><td>"awarded" before confirmation</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Roadmap / aspiration</td><td>"2026 priority," "planned," "roadmap target"</td><td>State as current fact</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

